GLADAFRICA Championship outfit Pretoria Callies FC have parted ways with head coach Sammy Troughton with immediate effect, the club have confirmed. Troughton spent over two seasons with the Romans and he was responsible for promoting the Tshwane outfit Championship ahead of the 2020-21 season. They are currently 11th on the Championship standings and are in the semi-finals of the Nedbank Cup where they will face Chippa United. "Sammy will remain part of Callies because we know what he’s capable of especially after promoting this team to the GladAfrica championship league,” said club chairman Moses Malada. “We wish him all the best in his career and once more we thank him for granting us the opportunity to work with him.”